Manchester City defender, Kyle Walker has reportedly married his childhood sweetheart at a secret wedding.  The Manchester City right-back, 31, reportedly tied the knot with his girlfriend of 12 years, Annie Kilner in a small ceremony at the end of November. Kyle met Annie when he was 18 while he was playing at his hometown club Sheffield United when the model was 16. The couple are parents to three children – Roman, Riaan, and Reign. In June 2020, the Mirror reported that Kyle had popped the question to Annie with an epic floral proposal at her home. Kyle also shares son Kairo, 14 months, with ex Lauryn Goodman. Although, he has never confirmed or denied that Kairo is his child.  Source Manchester (United Kingdom) -  Manchester City defender Kyle Walker’s love for former club Tottenham Hotspur will motivate him against Arsenal in the English League Cup final match on Sunday, the 27-year-old has said. The England international was involved in the north London derby on numerous occasions as he played 229… In "Sports" Manchester (UK) -  Gabriel Jesus scored twice as Manchester City beat Everton 3-1 on Saturday to pile the pressure on English Premier League title rivals Liverpool, who host Manchester United on Sunday. The win takes Pep Guardiola’s side, who lost for the first time in the league this season with… In "Sports" LONDON    - Paris St Germain right back Serge Aurier has been granted a United Kingdom work permit and is set to join Premier League club Tottenham Hotspur, according to media reports on Wednesday. Sky Sports said representatives of the 24-year-old Ivory Coast defender confirmed that a work permit had… In "Sports"